  "summary": "Possible typosquat of 'anthropic' with trivial payload",
  "details": "Package name 'anthropy' is one character edit away from the widely-used 'anthropic' Python SDK. The package contains a single module 'anthropy.py' whose only behavior is writing 'hello world!' to stdout. The pyproject.toml uses the standard hatchling build backend with no install hooks, and the package performs no network I/O, no subprocess execution, no credential or filesystem reads, and no obfuscation. The name proximity to a popular SDK creates confusion risk for developers who mistype the package name during install, but no installer-harm payload is present in this version.",
